{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775865644551,"sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","part":{"id":"prt_d79d74603001eU8vd10PW3xX27","messageID":"msg_d79d740de001E4FmV7KiQsDdPi","sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865688011,"sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","part":{"id":"prt_d79d757e5001gh90NUaiWPuYrY","messageID":"msg_d79d740de001E4FmV7KiQsDdPi","sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_9ef23a2781a74903a6579c56","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\n## Overview\n\nThis spec defines the `AgentRuntimeClient` — a high-level Python SDK client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane). It handles session bootstrapping, context manager lifecycle, and payload invocation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Construction\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that initializes connection parameters for Agent Runtime invocation via the Router.\n\n### Scenario: Constructor with all parameters\n- **GIVEN** a caller provides `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL store all provided values as attributes: `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`\n\n### Scenario: Constructor with defaults\n- **GIVEN** a caller provides only `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, `session_id` to `None`, `timeout` to `120`, and `connect_timeout` to `5.0`\n\n### Scenario: Router URL resolution from environment\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is not provided as an argument\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL read `router_url` from the `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n\n### Scenario: Router URL missing\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating that Router URL must be provided\n\n### Scenario: Data plane client initialization\n- **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`, storing it as `dp_client`\n\n### Scenario: Session ID bootstrapping when not provided\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` and assign the returned session ID to `self.session_id`\n\n### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID missing header\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n- **WHEN** `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **AND** the response does not contain the `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol for `AgentRuntimeClient` to ensure proper resource cleanup.\n\n### Scenario: Successful context manager usage\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to release resources\n\n### Scenario: Context manager usage with exception\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** an exception is raised inside the block\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL still call `close()` before propagating the exception\n\n### Scenario: Enter returns self\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Invoke Payload\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` method to send JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime and return the response.\n\n### Scenario: Successful invocation\n- **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is set on the client\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called with a dictionary payload\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload)` and return the response\n\n### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is set\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **THEN** the data plane invoke SHALL use `timeout=30.0` for the request\n\n### Scenario: Invoke without session ID\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy on the client\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Scenario: Invoke with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid and `timeout` argument is `None`\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n- **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n### Scenario: Invoke response handling\n- **GIVEN** a successful data plane response\n- **WHEN** `invoke` receives the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the response object (caller is responsible for parsing)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Close and Cleanup\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `close` method to release the underlying HTTP session resources.\n\n### Scenario: Close data plane session\n- **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeClient` with a `dp_client`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.close()` to close the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n### Scenario: Close without initialized data plane\n- **GIVEN** `dp_client` is `None` or not set\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL not raise an exception (no-op or safe guard)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: HTTP Client Contract — Agent Runtime Data Plane\n\nThe system SHALL use `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` to communicate with the Router for Agent Runtime invocations.\n\n### Scenario: Base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID via GET\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL send `GET` to `self.base_url` and read the `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n\n### Scenario: Invoke via POST\n- **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` and `payload`\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL send `POST` to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and body as JSON-serialized `payload`\n\n### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=None`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n\n### Scenario: Invoke with explicit timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=60.0`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60.0)` tuple\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Header Management\n\nThe system SHALL use the session header `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Agent Runtime data plane requests.\n\n### Scenario: Session header constant\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** accessing `SESSION_HEADER`\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n### Scenario: Session header on invoke request\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n- **WHEN** the POST request is constructed\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Logging\n\nThe system SHALL provide optional verbose logging for `AgentRuntimeClient` operations.\n\n### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is passed to constructor\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `logger` SHALL be configured at `DEBUG` level\n\n### Scenario: Verbose logging disabled\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=False` (default)\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `logger` SHALL be configured at `INFO` level or higher\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Exception Hierarchy Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with the AgentCube exception hierarchy for error handling.\n\n### Scenario: Data plane errors propagate\n- **GIVEN** the data plane returns an error response\n- **WHEN** `invoke` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL propagate the underlying `requests` exception or raise an appropriate `DataPlaneError`\n\n### Scenario: Network failure during bootstrap\n- **GIVEN** the Router is unreachable during `bootstrap_session_id()`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL propagate the `requests` exception (e.g., `ConnectionError`)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775865688001,"end":1775865688009}}}}
