{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865701634,"sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","part":{"id":"prt_d79d8211a001c4O9iNofYyQgIu","messageID":"msg_d79d8134f001f06TFJ5fyaEJqj","sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8e6936b091084a2895faa003","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient Initialization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL construct a `CodeInterpreterClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, then initializes internal clients for control plane and data plane communication.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Constructor with all defaults\n17: - **GIVEN** no arguments are passed to `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__`\n18: - **WHEN** the environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n19: - **THEN** the client SHALL initialize with `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`, and `router_url` from the environment\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n22: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n23: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Custom configuration\n27: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is constructed with explicit `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token`\n28: - **WHEN** the constructor completes\n29: - **THEN** all instance fields (`name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values, and `cp_client` SHALL be initialized with the control plane configuration\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Auth token from service account file\n32: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists\n33: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL read the token via `read_token_from_file` and set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on the session\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Auth token from service account file missing\n37: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and the SA token file does not exist\n38: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n39: - **THEN** `read_token_from_file` SHALL return `\"\"` and no `Authorization` header SHALL be set\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Session Lifecycle\n42: \n43: The system SHALL manage Code Interpreter sessions through creation, reuse, and deletion, with proper cleanup on context manager exit.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Session creation on init\n46: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided to the constructor\n47: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL call `cp_client.create_session(name, namespace, ttl=ttl)` and store the returned session ID\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Session reuse\n51: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to the constructor\n52: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT call `create_session` and SHALL use the provided `session_id` for data plane initialization\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Context manager entry\n56: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` statement\n57: - **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with normal flow\n61: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager and the block completes without exception\n62: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with `exc_type=None`\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n66: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager and an exception occurs in the block\n67: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with exception info\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL call `stop()` and SHALL NOT suppress the exception (return `None` or `False`)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Stop method cleanup\n71: - **GIVEN** `stop()` is called on a client with an active session\n72: - **WHEN** `stop()` executes\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL close the data plane client, delete the control plane session if `session_id` is set, and close the control plane client session\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Stop method idempotency\n76: - **GIVEN** `stop()` is called multiple times\n77: - **WHEN** subsequent calls execute\n78: - **THEN** they SHALL NOT raise errors (safe to call repeatedly)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Data Plane Initialization\n81: \n82: The system SHALL initialize the `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` after session creation, with proper error handling and cleanup on failure.\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Successful data plane init\n85: - **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is available\n86: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` is called\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL construct `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name=name`, and assign it to `self.dp_client`\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n90: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n91: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n92: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the exception\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Data plane init with existing session\n95: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was provided to the constructor\n96: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` is called\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL initialize the data plane client without attempting to delete any session on failure\n98: \n99: ### Requirement: Command Execution\n100: \n101: The system SHALL execute commands in the Code Interpreter session via the data plane API, with proper timeout handling and error reporting.\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Execute command success\n104: - **GIVEN** a valid session and data plane client\n105: - **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called\n106: - **THEN** it SHALL POST to `api/execute` with body `{\"command\": [\"echo hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and return the stdout from the response\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n109: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `timeout=30.0`\n110: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n111: - **THEN** the body SHALL include `\"timeout\": \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (timeout + 2.0 buffer)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n114: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `timeout=None`\n115: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n116: - **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL default to `120` seconds, body SHALL include `\"timeout\": \"120s\"`, and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n119: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n120: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n121: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` from the response\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Command as list\n124: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a list `[\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hi')\"]`\n125: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n126: - **THEN** the body SHALL include `\"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hi')\"]`\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Code Execution\n129: \n130: The system SHALL execute code snippets by writing them to temporary files and running the appropriate interpreter.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n133: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language=\"python\"` and some code\n134: - **WHEN** the method executes\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Python3 language alias\n138: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language=\"python3\"`\n139: - **WHEN** the method executes\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL treat it as Python and write a `.py` file\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Py language alias\n143: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language=\"py\"`\n144: - **WHEN** the method executes\n145: - **THEN** it SHALL treat it as Python and write a `.py` file\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Unsupported language\n148: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with an unsupported `language`\n149: - **WHEN** the method executes\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the language is not supported\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: File Operations\n153: \n154: The system SHALL provide file upload, download, write, and listing operations through the data plane API.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Write file\n157: - **GIVEN** `write_file` is called with `content` and `remote_path`\n158: - **WHEN** the method executes\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": remote_path, \"content\": <base64-encoded>, \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Upload file\n162: - **GIVEN** `upload_file` is called with `local_path` and `remote_path`\n163: - **WHEN** the method executes\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL POST multipart to `api/files` with `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': remote_path, 'mode': '0644'}`, including `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Download file\n167: - **GIVEN** `download_file` is called with `remote_path` and `local_path`\n168: - **WHEN** the method executes\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` (where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) and write the response content to `local_path`\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: List files\n172: - **GIVEN** `list_files` is called with `path=\".\"`\n173: - **WHEN** the method executes\n174: - **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files` with query parameter `path=.` and return the response\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: List files with custom path\n177: - **GIVEN** `list_files` is called with `path=\"/tmp\"`\n178: - **WHEN** the method executes\n179: - **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files` with query parameter `path=/tmp`\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: HTTP Client Configuration\n182: \n183: The system SHALL configure HTTP clients with appropriate connection pooling, timeouts, and headers for both control plane and data plane communication.\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Control plane session configuration\n186: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n187: - **WHEN** the session is created\n188: - **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted for `http://` and `https://` with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`, and default headers `Content-Type: application/json`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Data plane session configuration\n191: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized\n192: - **WHEN** the session is created\n193: - **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`, and default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Data plane base URL construction\n196: - **GIVEN** `base_url` is not provided to `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n197: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Data plane explicit base URL\n201: - **GIVEN** `base_url` is explicitly provided to `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n202: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n203: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly without constructing from `router_url`\n204: \n205: ### Requirement: Timeout Defaults\n206: \n207: The system SHALL apply consistent timeout defaults across all HTTP operations, with per-call override support.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Control plane default timeouts\n210: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n211: - **WHEN** any request is made\n212: - **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Data plane default timeouts\n215: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n216: - **WHEN** any request is made\n217: - **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` unless overridden per-call\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Execute command timeout buffer\n220: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a numeric `timeout` value\n221: - **WHEN** the HTTP request is made\n222: - **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `timeout + 2.0` seconds to prevent premature `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Exception Hierarchy\n225: \n226: The system SHALL define and use a consistent exception hierarchy for error handling.\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n229: - **GIVEN** a command fails with non-zero exit code\n230: - **WHEN** `CommandExecutionError` is raised\n231: - **THEN** it SHALL have attributes `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`, and the message SHALL include `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: AgentCubeError base class\n234: - **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, or `DataPlaneError` is raised\n235: - **WHEN** caught as `AgentCubeError`\n236: - **THEN** it SHALL be catchable since all are subclasses of `AgentCubeError`\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: SessionError definition\n239: - **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n240: - **WHEN** imported\n241: - **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError` with docstring `\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"`\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: DataPlaneError definition\n244: - **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n245: - **WHEN** imported\n246: - **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError` with docstring `\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"`\n247: \n248: ### Requirement: Logging\n249: \n250: The system SHALL provide configurable logging for debugging and operational visibility.\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n253: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is constructed with `verbose=True`\n254: - **WHEN** operations are performed\n255: - **THEN** the logger SHALL output debug-level messages\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Default logging level\n258: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is constructed with `verbose=False` (default)\n259: - **WHEN** operations are performed\n260: - **THEN** the logger SHALL output at `INFO` level or higher\n261: \n262: ### Requirement: Public API Surface\n263: \n264: The system SHALL export only the intended public classes from the package.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Root package exports\n267: - **GIVEN** `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n268: - **WHEN** the import succeeds\n269: - **THEN** both classes SHALL be accessible and `agentcube.__all__` SHALL contain exactly `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Clients submodule exports\n272: - **GIVEN** `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n273: - **WHEN** the import succeeds\n274: - **THEN** all three classes SHALL be accessible and `agentcube.clients.__all__` SHALL contain exactly `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n275: \n276: ## File Changes\n277: \n278: | Action | File | Description |\n279: |--------|------|-------------|\n280: | Create | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports for `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n281: | Create | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` class with context manager support |\n282: | Create | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class |\n283: | Create | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`) |\n284: | Create | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports for internal client classes |\n285: | Create | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager API |\n286: | Create | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` for Router data plane API |\n287: | Create | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Agent Runtime data plane |\n288: | Create | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` helper with HTTPAdapter mounting |\n289: | Create | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` helper |\n290: | Create | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` helper |\n291: | Create | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty module marker |\n292: | Create | `pyproject.toml` | Package configuration with dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT`, `cryptography`) |\n\n(End of file - total 292 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct a `CodeInterpreterClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, then initializes internal clients for control plane and data plane communication.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all defaults\n- **GIVEN** no arguments are passed to `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__`\n- **WHEN** the environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **THEN** the client SHALL initialize with `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`, and `router_url` from the environment\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775865701615,"end":1775865701631}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775865701692,"sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","part":{"id":"prt_d79d8252c00106NO3wb218EkEe","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79d8134f001f06TFJ5fyaEJqj","sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":31433,"input":31265,"output":80,"reasoning":88,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.008906508}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775865707771,"sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","part":{"id":"prt_d79d83cf90019OPjZkT9D3WDKQ","messageID":"msg_d79d82554001OGn6POxtQKroE1","sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865800799,"sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","part":{"id":"prt_d79d841aa001sTiRWBfRmFFRBm","messageID":"msg_d79d82554001OGn6POxtQKroE1","sessionID":"ses_28628cb42ffeXsEdOPjvwwFLwu","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_e83f0421e42f4ce3b1df2e3b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, bootstraps a session ID via the data plane, and initializes the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all arguments\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with explicit `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`\n- **WHEN** the constructor completes\n- **THEN** all instance fields (`agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with only `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** the constructor completes\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, `session_id` to `None`, `timeout` to `120`, and `connect_timeout` to `5.0`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is not provided as an argument\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL read `router_url` from the `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client initialization\n- **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`, storing it as `self.dp_client`\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID bootstrapping when not provided\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` and assign the returned value to `self.session_id`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID missing header\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n- **WHEN** `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **AND** the response does not contain the `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID reuse when provided\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to the constructor\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()` and SHALL use the provided `session_id` directly\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol for `AgentRuntimeClient` to ensure proper resource cleanup on block exit.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used in a `with` statement\n- **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with normal flow\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager and the block completes without exception\n- **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with `exc_type=None`\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `close()` to clean up resources\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager and an exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with exception info\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `close()` and SHALL NOT suppress the exception (return `None` or `False`)\n\n### Requirement: Invoke Payload\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` method to send JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint and return the response.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful invocation\n- **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is set on the client\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called with a dictionary payload\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload)` and return the `requests.Response` object\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy on the client\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **THEN** the data plane invoke SHALL use `timeout=30.0` for the request\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid and `timeout` argument is `None`\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n- **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke response handling\n- **GIVEN** a successful data plane response\n- **WHEN** `invoke` receives the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the response object without parsing (caller is responsible for JSON deserialization)\n\n### Requirement: Close and Cleanup\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `close` method to release the underlying HTTP session resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Close data plane session\n- **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeClient` with a `dp_client`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.close()` to close the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n#### Scenario: Close without initialized data plane\n- **GIVEN** `dp_client` is `None` or not set\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT raise an exception (no-op or safe guard)\n\n#### Scenario: Close idempotency\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called multiple times\n- **WHEN** subsequent calls execute\n- **THEN** they SHALL NOT raise errors (safe to call repeatedly)\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL bootstrap a session ID by sending a GET request to the invocation base URL and reading the response header.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID via GET\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL send `GET` to `self.base_url` and read the `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** the GET response contains header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123`\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` parses the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap missing session header\n- **GIVEN** the GET response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke\n\nThe system SHALL send POST requests to the invocation base URL with session headers and JSON payload.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke via POST\n- **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` and `payload`\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL send `POST` to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and body as JSON-serialized `payload`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=None`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with explicit timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=60.0`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60.0)` tuple\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke response return\n- **GIVEN** the POST request completes\n- **WHEN** `invoke` finishes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the `requests.Response` object without parsing\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Base URL\n\nThe system SHALL construct the invocation base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n### Requirement: Session Header Management\n\nThe system SHALL use the session header `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Agent Runtime data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Session header constant\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** accessing `SESSION_HEADER`\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Session header on invoke request\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n- **WHEN** the POST request is constructed\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session header on bootstrap GET\n- **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n- **THEN** the request SHALL use the session default headers only (no explicit session header needed for bootstrap)\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Client Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure the HTTP client with appropriate connection pooling and timeout defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane session configuration\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** any request is made\n- **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n\n### Requirement: Logging\n\nThe system SHALL provide configurable logging for `AgentRuntimeClient` operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** operations are performed\n- **THEN** the logger SHALL output debug-level messages\n\n#### Scenario: Default logging level\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with `verbose=False` (default)\n- **WHEN** operations are performed\n- **THEN** the logger SHALL output at `INFO` level or higher\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class with context manager support |\n| Create | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Agent Runtime data plane |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775865800783,"end":1775865800797}}}}
